; Regression test for issue #1082: A change in precision used on an amount in-stream affects the balancing precision of following transactions (BZ#1082)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1082
;
; When a high-precision amount appears in the journal, the $ commodity's
; precision increases and all subsequent (and even prior) $ amounts are
; displayed at the higher precision. Here $5.5555 causes $10.00 and $3.00
; to be displayed as $10.0000 and $3.0000.

2024/01/01 Normal precision
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash      -$10.00

2024/01/02 High precision
    Expenses:Bar     $5.5555
    Assets:Cash      -$5.5555

2024/01/03 After precision change
    Expenses:Food    $3.00
    Assets:Cash      -$3.00

test bal
           $-18.5555  Assets:Cash
            $18.5555  Expenses
             $5.5555    Bar
            $13.0000    Food
--------------------
                   0
end test

test reg
24-Jan-01 Normal precision      Expenses:Food              $10.0000     $10.0000
                                Assets:Cash               $-10.0000            0
24-Jan-02 High precision        Expenses:Bar                $5.5555      $5.5555
                                Assets:Cash                $-5.5555            0
24-Jan-03 After precision cha.. Expenses:Food               $3.0000      $3.0000
                                Assets:Cash                $-3.0000            0
end test
